data.story: The adidas Yeezy Slide Infants ‘Onyx’ updates the minimalist slip-on silhouette with a monochrome black finish. The stealthy design is executed on a one-piece build made with injected EVA foam. An adjustable strap wraps around the heel for a secure fit. adidas’ three-stripe branding is debossed on the footbed, featuring a soft top layer for step-in comfort. Underfoot, deep grooves are built into the outsole, yielding a flexible ride, grippy traction, and improved shock absorption.

adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Light (Infant)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infants ‘Light’ carries a re-engineered Primeknit upper in a muted ivory finish, accented with a post-dyed monofilament side stripe that adds a see-through element to the sock-like build. The shoe is updated with UV-sensitive technology, meaning direct sunlight causes the Primeknit construction to become tinged in pink, while the side stripe reveals a dark amber hue. The lightweight build is mounted on a responsive Boost midsole, wrapped in a rubber cage for added support and durability.

data.name: Marvel x Stan Smith Infant 'Hulk Smash'
data.story: The Marvel x adidas Stan Smith Infant ‘Hulk Smash’ is drawn from a sustainable collection celebrating an eclectic cast of characters from the Disney, Pixar, Marvel and Star Wars universes. This pair gives the nod to the Incredible Hulk, featuring a black Primegreen upper made with 50% recycled content. ‘It’s not easy being green’ is inscribed across the bright green heel tab of each shoe, while a ‘Hulk Smash!’ graphic adorns the lateral quarter panel. A crisp white rubber cupsole anchors the low-top.

data.story: The adidas Yeezy 450 Infants ‘Dark Slate’ treats Kanye West’s futuristic silhouette to a stealthy finish. This scaled-down version for little feet makes use of a charcoal grey knit upper, accented with a subtle brownish tone along the heel. Lace-up closure combines with an elastic cuff to provide a snug, comfortable fit. The sneaker rides on a solid black EVA midsole, highlighted by tapered ‘fingers’ that wrap up the side panels. Exterior branding is limited to an adidas logo hit on the wavy outsole.

adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bright Cyan (Infant)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Infant ‘Bright Cyan’ showcases a sleek, seamless upper in highlighter-blue coloring. The sneaker’s lightweight polyester construction is dominated by silver reflective ‘700’ branding on the lateral side. Contrasting black no-sew overlays offer added support and durability, while no-tie bungee laces provide easy on and off. The sculpted polyurethane midsole is enhanced with full-length drop-in Boost cushioning, visible through cutaway detailing on the herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

data.name: Kevin Lyons x Superstar Infant 'Create Your Future'
data.story: Launching as part of a kids collection with the Brooklyn-based artist, the Kevin Lyons x adidas Superstar Infant ‘Create Your Future’ reimagines the classic shell-toed sneaker as a slip-on silhouette with dual hook-and-loop straps. The white synthetic leather upper, composed of at least 50% recycled materials, features serrated black three-stripes inscribed with the phrase ‘Create Your Future.’ Additional embellishments include paint splatter on the eyestay and a graphic depicting one of Lyons’ signature monsters on the lateral side.

data.name: Yeezy Boost 380 Infants 'Alien Blue'
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Infants ‘Alien Blue’ utilizes a flexible Primeknit upper in a subtle blend of cream and grey hues. A fluorescent shade of green distinguishes the monofilament window that’s woven into the side panel, improving the shoe’s breathability while adding a see-through design element to the sock-like build. No-tie laces and a stretchy knit collar allow for easy on and off. The sneaker is mounted on a full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in a blue-tinged rubber cage and supported underfoot by a herringbone-traction outsole.

Monsters Inc. x Stan Smith Infant 'Mike Wazowski'
data.story: The Monsters Inc. x adidas Stan Smith Infant ‘Mike Wazowski’ is taken from a larger Disney collection that pays homage to the green-skinned characters that populate the studio’s expansive universe. A graphic print featuring the one-eyed monster from the hit 2001 Pixar film is plastered across the Primegreen upper, made with 50% recycled content and finished in a subtle off-white hue. The tongue tag on the right shoe displays Stan Smith’s likeness, the left features Mike’s, and the Trefoil branded heel tabs are marked with the tagline ‘It’s Not Easy Being Green.’ A translucent rubber cuposle in a neon green finish anchors the low-profile silhouette.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Ash Pearl (Infant)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infants ‘Ash Pearl’ outfits a scaled-down version of the sock-like sneaker in a neutral-hued Primeknit upper. The lateral side is rendered in split color blocking, featuring a blend of subtle tan shades across the vamp, collar and monofilament side stripe. They’re joined by a greyscale finish on the lower portion of the shoe, and throughout the medial side in an uninterrupted patchwork arrangement. A rubber-wrapped Boost midsole offers a cushioned ride.

adidas Yeezy 380 Covellite (Infants)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Infants ‘Covellite’ offers sock-like comfort for growing feet. Finished in varying blue shades, the re-engineered Primeknit upper is equipped with no-tie stretch laces for easy on and off. A translucent monofilament window is woven directly into the knit construction for textural depth and added breathability. The sneaker sits atop a full-length Boost midsole, reinforced with wrapped sidewalls and a herringbone-tread gum rubber outsole.

data.name: adidas Yeezy 450 Cloud White (Infant)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy 450 Infant ‘Cloud White’ presents the debut colorway of a futuristic Yeezy model scaled down for little feet. Decorative no-tie stretch laces are integrated into the flexible knit upper, featuring an elastic cuff for a sock-like fit. A molded EVA midsole combines with an Ortholite sockliner to deliver lightweight cushioning, while its unique structure forms a supportive cage. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a wavy traction pattern for added grip.

data.name: ZX 2K Infant 'Wordmark Heel Stripe - White'
data.story: The adidas ZX 2K Infant ‘Wordmark Heel Stripe’ provides a modern take on the brand’s ZX running heritage for little feet. A crisp white finish is executed on the lightweight textile upper, accented with a seamless overlay that wraps around the heel and features a repeating adidas wordmark in white-on-navy block lettering. Plush cushioning comes courtesy of an exaggerated foam midsole, partially caged for rearfoot support and durability.

data.name: Swift Run X Infant 'White Iridescent'
data.story: The adidas Swift Run X Infant ‘White Iridescent’ delivers running shoe comfort for little feet. Inspired by archival track shoes, the sneaker makes use of a white textile upper with iridescent purple three-stripes. Interior bootie construction provides a snug, comfortable fit, while an EVA midsole offers lightweight cushioning with each step. Underfoot, flex grooves are built into the black rubber outsole, resulting in a traction pattern that promotes the natural motion of the foot.

data.name: Flex Infant 'White Glow Blue'
data.story: The adidas Flex Infant ‘White Glow Blue’ features bootie-style construction and a stretchy mesh upper ideally suited for little feet. Parents can choose between standard or elastic laces, which can be fed through multiple eyelets for a custom fit. A pull loop at the heel provides easy on and off, while synthetic overlays deliver added support and durability. The sneaker rests on an EVA sole unit with flex grooves underfoot that promote a natural stride.

data.name: Flex Infant 'Black White'
data.story: The adidas Flex Infant ‘Black White’ features an elemental palette on a versatile sneaker made for little feet. Bootie-style construction is used on the stretchy black textile upper, equipped with a convenient pull tab and secured with a lacing system that incorporates multiple eyelets for a custom fit. The sneaker is mounted on a crisp white foam sole unit that offers lightweight cushioning with each step. Underfoot, flex grooves provide no-slip traction while promoting natural movement.

data.name: adidas Yeezy 380 Yecoraite Reflective (Infants)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Infants ‘Yecoraite’ offers sock-like comfort for little feet, featuring a Primeknit upper equipped with decorative no-tie laces and a snug, elastic collar. A blend of grey and off-white tones is contrasted by a translucent monofilament window in a diluted orange hue. The minimalist silhouette sits atop a full-length Boost midsole, enveloped in a semi-translucent rubber cage and supported by a herringbone rubber outsole in a subtle coral finish.

data.name: NASA x ZX 2K Infant 'Cloud White Grey'
data.story: Taken from a larger collection made in partnership with the American space agency, the NASA x adidas ZX 2K Infant ‘Cloud White Grey’ delivers a scaled-down version of a lifestyle runner meant to channel the pioneering spirt of the ZX franchise. Metallic silver detailing is applied to the sneaker’s signature three-stripes and EVA midsole, the latter blending in bright orange coloring for an eye-catching gradient effect. The tongue tag features an Artemis insignia in a nod to NASA’s lunar mission program.

data.name: NASA x ZX 2K Infant 'Dash Grey Silver'
data.story: Made for a new generation of space lovers, the NASA x adidas ZX 2K Infant ‘Dash Grey Silver’ celebrates the American space agency with NASA-branded insoles and Artemis tongue tags — a nod to the program aiming to return astronauts to the moon by 2024. The neutral grey textile upper, enlivened with neon accents and metallic silver three-stripes, sits atop a partially caged EVA midsole finished in a gradient blend of black and silver.

The low-top makes use of a white leather upper with contrasting black three-stripes and a heel tab in High-Res Red. Dual adidas and Run DMC branding adorns the printed tongue tag and mesh sockliner. data.name: Tensaur Run I Infant 'Black Signal Pink'

Dual hook-and-loop straps and a webbing pull tab enable little feet to slip easily into the shoe, featuring a black mesh upper with tonal synthetic overlays at the toe and heel. Floating three-stripes and decorative stitch detailing are rendered in Signal Pink, offering sharpy contrasting pops of color. An EVA sole unit anchors the lightweight build.

data.name: Tensaur Run I Infant 'Legacy Blue'
data.story: The adidas Tensaur Run I Infant ‘Legacy Blue’ features a lightweight, comfortable build tailored for little feet. data.story: The adidas Superstar Infant ‘International Girls’ Day’ celebrates the empowerment of young girls with a color-blocked take on the classic silhouette. Half the upper utilizes traditional white leather construction with black leather three-stripes, while the sneaker’s forefoot is rendered in an eclectic mix of colors. Teal textile paneling is combined with a neon green shell toe and bright orange accenting on the laces, tongue and eyestay. Split coloring extends to the midsole, separated by white and off-white hues.

data.name: ZX 2K Infant 'Gradient'
data.story: The adidas ZX 2K Infant ‘Gradient’ delivers a miniaturized version of a sneaker that channels the streamlined aesthetic of adidas’ early ZX 000 series. A ventilated white mesh upper, secured with no-tie elastic and equipped with a convenient pull tab, sits atop a full-length EVA midsole. A gradient blue and purple finish is applied to the TPU cage that wraps around the heel for added stability and a vibrant pop of color.

data.name: ZX 2K Flux Infant 'White Signal Cyan'
data.story: Made for little feet, the adidas ZX 2K Flux Infant ‘White Signal Cyan’ offers lightweight comfort in a sneaker that takes its design cues from classic ZX models of the ‘80s and ‘90s. Breathable grey mesh is secured with no-tie elastic laces and reinforced with bright blue no-sew overlays for added durability and support. The multicolor composition up top is offset by a full-length EVA midsole in a pristine white finish.

data.name: FortaRun X CF I 'Core Black'
data.story: The adidas FortaRun X CF I sneaker supports growing feet in a technical construction with an athletic-inspired, modern look. This kid's version—revealed in July 2019—holds a Core Black mesh and TPU upper keeping the foot contained via a hook-and-loop with Three-Stripes detailing. Motivational text is written on the heel pull. The one-piece EVA sole is lightweight and traction-ready thanks to a chevron tread pattern.

data.name: FortaRun X CF I 'Real Pink'
data.story: Delivering superior cushioning and lightweight stability, the running-inspired adidas FortaRun X CF I 'Real Pink' sneaker helps comfort growing feet. Released in July 2019, this kids’ shoe is dressed in a vibrant colorway, constructed with a flexible mesh upper. A Velcro hook-and-loop strap provides locked down stability. Underfoot, EVA foam and a durable rubber sole work together for plush, yet resilient support.

data.name: NMD 360 I 'Core Black'
data.story: The adidas NMD 360 I is based on the original streetwear-inspired sneaker and its racing heritage. Released in July 2019, this kid's iteration sports reflective Three-Stripes on a Core Black mesh bootie with a reinforced forefoot and slip-on style. Custom branding details the tongue loop and pull tab underlaying the molded leather heel badge. The sneaker's lightweight EVA sole is stabilized by brightly colored plugs.

data.name: Forest Grove CF I 'Collegiate Royal'
data.story: The adidas Forest Grove CF I brings the Oregon running shoe back to life with a modern shape and kid-specific styling. Produced in July 2019, this update flaunts Collegiate Royal textile and suede for the upper, a branded leather heel tab and vibrant Three-Stripes. A dual-strap closure provides a locked-down feel. Webbing across the EVA sole makes a nod to the shock-absorbing web that wrapped around the original's midsole.

data.name: Forest Grove CF I 'Active Orange'
data.story: Molded after the groundbreaking 1982 marathon running shoe, the Oregon, the Forest Grove effortlessly blends classic 80s style with updated technology and design. adidas repackaged the adult-sized shoe into a kids’ sized version for the July 2019 release of the adidas Forest Grove CF I 'Active Orange' sneaker. Synthetic suede and mesh cover the upper, strapped down Velcro hook-and-loop closures, while EVA foam cushions below.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Synth (Infant)
data.story: Released regionally in June 2019, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infant 'Synth' sneaker represents Kanye West's progressive, nonconformist design aesthetic. Patterned rope laces and a signature monofilament stripe are integrated into the sneaker's two-tone Primeknit bootie. The Three-Stripes emblem adorns the interior heel. A tubular sole powered by Boost technology helps ensure a comfortable step.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Antlia (Infant)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infant 'Antlia Non-Reflective' formats the June 2019 release for little feet. The 'Antlia' colorway, both in reflective and non-reflective iterations, was exclusively released in Europe. This infant-sized take includes a Primeknit upper with a semi-translucent window at the lateral, much like the original 350 V2 released in 2016. For an update, this shoe does without the heel tab and casts the upper in a pale yellow-green tone. Full-length Boost cushioning promotes comfort within a TPU cage, underscored by rubber tread.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Vanta (Infant)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 'Vanta' was offered up in this infant-sized iteration for a June 2019 release. The shoe features a futuristic, multi-layer mesh upper with suede overlays, just like the larger sizes. The Yeezy 700 V2 features a similar chunky midsole compared to the V1, which debuted at Kanye West's Season 5 fashion show in 2017. The midsole houses full-length adidas Boost cushioning for responsive comfort.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Glow (Infant)
data.story: Emerged in May 2019, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 GID Infant 'Glow' sneaker is a high-vis execution of the cult icon. Its Primeknit bootie sports a fluorescent green hue that illuminates in the dark. Custom tooling comprises the heel pull, rope laces and a translucent monofilament stripe across the lateral side. Boost cushioning encased in a translucent rubber Tubular sole provides energized stability.

data.name: FortaSwim I 'Core Pink'
data.story: The adidas FortaSwim I 'Core Pink' adds style to the functional kids’ swim shoe with a bright all-pink color scheme. Constructed with mesh and synthetic materials for a breathable design, the shoe incorporates a sturdy ankle strap, cutouts at the ankle and sides, an adjustable midfoot strap and a durable closed toe. Stylish details like the adidas Three-Stripes logo are seen across the midfoot in white, with a tonal pink textured sole to complete the look.

data.name: FortaSwim I 'Core Blue'
data.story: The adidas FortaSwim I 'Core Blue' takes on a bright blue and orange colorway in this skillfully designed, closed-toe swim shoe for kids. Designed with a mesh and synthetic upper, the breathable design incorporates an ankle strap with an adjustable hook and loop strap across the midfoot to ensure a snug and secure fit. Side cutouts help with air circulation and a durable rounded toe helps protect feet.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Clay (Infant)
data.story: Debuting in late March, 2019, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Clay' marked the first time a 350 would be released in adult, kids and infant sizes. The infant-sized Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infant 'Clay' mimics the larger versions, with a Primeknit upper that features a variety of patterns in orange-brown with a horizontal contrast stripe. A bright orange heel tab adds an accent, and the silhouette sits atop a translucent midsole and rubber outsole.

data.name: RapidaZen I 'Red'
data.story: With streetwear styling and a running-inspired design, the adidas RapidaZen I was created to support little ones during playtime. This option features a red textile and mesh upper covered in a camouflage graphic, a synthetic toe guard and reinforced counter. A Badge of Sport logo adorns the tongue. The sneaker's one-piece sole unit is cushioned and has deep siping to promote natural flexing of the foot.

data.name: Gazelle 360 I 'Collegiate Royal'
data.story: Outfitted for growing feet, the adidas Gazelle 360 I sneaker is a kids’ version of the classic training shoe from 1966. The 'Collegiate Royal' edition updates the stretchy, faux-suede upper with a convenient, slip-on design. Signature details, such as serrated, Bold Gold Three-Stripes branding on the sidewall and a matching heel tab with adidas Trefoil branding, deliver the iconic look of the original Gazelle shoe. A flexible EVA outsole adds support.

data.name: Gazelle 360 I 'Scarlet'
data.story: The adidas Gazelle 360 I sneaker is a kids’ version of the timeless training shoe from 1966. Styled for growing feet, the ‘Scarlet’ rendition swaps out the lacing system for a lightweight, slip-on design. It sports a Grey One synthetic suede upper highlighted by Scarlet overlays throughout. Three-Stripes branding on the sidewall and a matching heel tab with adidas Trefoil branding deliver the same look as the adult version, with an Ortholite sockliner and flexible EVA outsole underfoot.

data.name: Superstar 360 I 'Clear Orange'
data.story: The adidas Superstar 360 I sneaker recodes the 80s classic through simplified lines and signature detailing. Presented in March 2019, this 'Clear Orange' kids' variation is fitted with an innovative slip-on textile bootie featuring an iconic shell toe, a serrated Three-Stripes emblem and additional branding found on the tongue and quarter. Deep hexagonal flex grooves complete the contrast EVA outsole.

data.name: RapidaZen I 'Black'
data.story: A minimalist expression of its athletic heritage, the adidas RapidaZen I is a modern sneaker inspired by running. Originally revealed in March 2019, this laceless kids' option features an adaptive mesh upper with strategic ventilation, an extended tongue and reflective paneling. Dual-type logos imbue retro brand DNA into the look. Molded ribbing wraps the sidewall of the abrasion-resistant EVA outsole.

data.name: Disney x FortaRun AC I 'Minnie'
data.story: The lightweight adidas FortaRun silhouette gets a Disney makeover with the Disney x FortaRun AC I 'Minnie' sneaker. The kids’ shoe features a mesh upper decorated with whimsical striped polka dots, accented by Minnie Mouse’s famous red bow and reinforced with supportive overlays and a Velcro closure. An EcoOrthoLite sockliner combines with an abrasion-resistant EVA outsole to help provide optimal comfort and durability.

data.name: Superstar 360 I 'Blue'
data.story: A fresh translation of the 80s icon, the adidas Superstar 360 I keeps the retro spirit alive in a pared-down design. Revealed in February 2019, this 'Blue' kids' version delivers low-top coverage in a stretchy neoprene bootie adorned with reflective Three-Stripes, a branded leather heel patch and a signature rubber shell toe. An EVA outsole detailed with deep hexagonal flex grooves sits underfoot.

data.name: Superstar 360 I 'Pink'
data.story: The adidas Superstar 360 I sneaker simplifies the 80s-popularized icon in an updated profile with retro distinction. Issued in February 2019, this 'Pink' kids' variant is shaped by a neoprene upper with an innovative slip-on design. An iconic shell toe, tonal Three-Stripes and reflective branding elements impart signature style and functionality. The contrast EVA outsole bolsters the body, flexing with hexagonal grooves.

data.name: Disney x FortaRun AC I 'Mickey'
data.story: Disney joins forces with adidas for the playful kids’ shoe, the Disney x FortaRun AC I 'Mickey' sneaker. It’s outfitted with a seamless mesh upper embroidered with a striped Mickey Mouse print. The hook-and-loop strap closure is also fitted with Mickey, a silhouette of the iconic mouse. An ultralight EcoOrthoLite sockliner, Cloudfoam midsole and one-piece EVA outsole work together to provide little feet cushioned comfort.

data.name: Superstar CF I 'Scarlet'
data.story: The adidas Superstar CF I reworks the 1969 court icon in a kids'-specific design with signature features. Revealed in January 2019, the 'Scarlet' Three-Stripes and logos are emblazoned on this leather edition featuring a padded tongue, triple-strap closure, rubber shell toe and perforations. A lightweight EVA midsole and treaded rubber outsole offer support below.

data.name: Superstar 360 I 'Scarlet'
data.story: The adidas Superstar 360 I 'Scarlet' sneaker rethinks the style's heritage-inspired design with signature details and an updated profile. Issued in January 2019, this 'Scarlet' kids' version provides a stretchy fit in a one-piece textile bootie with a reflective heel patch and pull tab. Serrated Three-Stripes, a classic shell toe and contrast branding are reminiscent of the original. A grooved EVA outsole provides a flexible step.

data.name: FortaRun X CF I 'Pink'
data.story: Modeled after the women’s Edgebounce runner, the adidas FortaRun X CF I 'Pink' sneaker takes cues from the adult version and repackages it for a girls'-specific fit. The kids’-sized shoe features a breathable mesh upper dressed in a tonal colorway. Tongue and heel pulls along with a stretch hook-and-loop strap closure, provide adjustable comfort and support. An abrasion-resistant EVA outsole protects little feet from play.

data.name: StarWars x RapidaZen I
data.story: With a wide foot, stretchy material and a slip-on construction, the kids'-sized adidas StarWars x RapidaZen I provides easy on and off for tiny feet. The infants' shoe also has a cushioned insole and a soft sockliner to keep them comfortable. A black-and-white Star Wars motif covers much of the upper, with a heel counter and outsole in black. The overlays and midsole ridges add durability and round out the look.

data.name: Duramo 9 I 'Granite Mint'
data.story: Whether it’s worn on or off the pavement, the adidas Duramo 9 I 'Granite Mint' sneaker is a versatile silhouette for growing feet. The kids’-sized shoe is constructed of a breathable mesh upper, padded with a soft collar and tongue. It’s reinforced with bungee laces and an adjustable Velcro strap for extra security. Sitting underfoot, the cushioned insole and midsole help deliver comfort for each footfall.

data.story: First released on April 29, 2017, alongside the identical adult model, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infant ‘Cream White’ combines a cream Primeknit upper with tonal cream SPLY 350 branding, and a translucent white midsole housing full-length Boost.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black Red (Infant)
data.story: First released on February 11, 2017, alongside the identical adult model, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 infant ‘Bred’ combines a black Primeknit upper with red SPLY 350 branding, and a translucent black midsole housing full-length Boost.

adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (Infant)
data.story: Released on August 24th, 2016, alongside the Yeezy Boost 350 Infant ‘Turtle Dove’ colorway, the Yeezy Boost 350 Infant ‘Pirate Black’ 2016 is an exact replica of the adult model in infant sizes from 5 to 10. The design features a pirate black/dark grey Primeknit upper with branded suede patches on the medial sides, patterned dark grey rope laces, red accented heel tabs, and a black Boost outsole.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtledove (Infant)
data.story: Released on August 24th, 2016, alongside the Yeezy Boost 350 Infant ‘Pirate Black’ 2016 colorway, the Yeezy Boost 350 Infant ‘Turtle Dove’ is an exact replica of the adult model in infant sizes from 5 to 10. The design features a blue-gray/turtle dove Primeknit upper with branded suede patches on the medial sides, patterned rope laces, red accented heel tabs, and a white Boost outsole.

data.name: Samoa Leather TD
data.story: The iconic 1982 Samoa became a classic with its easy-going, casual style and design. The adidas Samoa Leather TD takes elements from the adult sneaker and inserts into a kid’s sized version. A bright, vivid hue envelops the upper, outfitted in premium leather. Serrated Three-Stripes accent the shoe, along with a contrast heel tab and toe guard. Designed for growing feet, a web-patterned midsole and Trefoil branded outsole provide responsive cushioning.

data.name: Gazelle I 'Mini Rodini'
data.story: adidas teamed up with Swedish children's clothing maker, Mini Rodini for the August 2017 release of the Gazelle I 'Mini Rodini' sneaker. This take on the classic training sneaker dresses the polyester upper with a cheerful cactus print. The shoe's Three-Stripes are reprised in synthetic leather, adjacent to metallic gold 'Gazelle' branding. An OrthoLite sockliner and micro-cell patterned rubber tread add comfort and grip.

data.name: Jeremy Scott x Wings 2.0 I 'Triple Black'
data.story: adidas and Jeremy Scott's iconic Wings 2.0 silhouette gets the 'Triple Black' treatment through this glossy, September 2013 release. Based on the adult version, this kids' sized sneaker incorporates a patent upper in a fully black colorway. Not to be overlooked, the shoe's distinctive wing panels add avant-garde flair, while Three-Stripes branding offers low-key heritage ties. Jeremy Scott branding identifies the shoe besides a white grid-patterned section on the midsole.

data.name: Tubular Radial El I 'White Metallic Silver'
data.story: The adidas Tubular Radial El I remixes the iconic '93 design with playful updates for kids. Released in January 2017, this edition flaunts a white neoprene upper with an elastic midfoot strap and a synthetic toe guard. Its signature Three-Stripes lace cage and Trefoil heel panel shine with an iridescent finish. The matching rubber sole aims to give the shoe a boost in traction with its rippled tread.

Superstar I 'Triple Black'
data.story: The adidas Superstar made a name for itself over many decades, thanks largely to its signature rubber shell toe. The Superstar I 'Triple Black' adds to the legacy by dipping the traditional leather upper all in black. This kids' edition retains the key aspects of the heritage style, including classic Trefoil tongue and heel branding, serrated Three-Stripes and a herringbone-treaded rubber outsole.

data.name: Disney x RapidaZen Sum Infant 'Mickey Mouse'
Jeremy Scott x Leopard Infant
data.story: Teaming up with fashion designer Jeremy Scott, the Three-Stripes brand unveiled this leopard-inspired design in 2011. The Jeremy Scott x Leopard Infant edition is sized down for kids and includes a furry, animal-print upper. This stand-out shoe is complete with a springy tail, pushing the theme past normal limits. The mid-cut shoe includes brown Three-Stripes detailing on the sidewall and a firm sole construction to match.

This infant shoe is a playful take on formal wear in full-grain leather, embellished with a white panel and bow. Signature Three-Stripes detailing is stitched on the sides. Co-branding on the insole denotes the collaboration. A treaded outsole reinforces the construction.

Samoa I 'Core Black'
data.story: The adidas Samoa I ‘Core Black’ sneaker is an iconic classic shoe for everyday wear with a comfortable textile lining. A synthetic leather all-black upper is decorated with the iconic Three-Stripes branding on the quarter panel, perforated details throughout, and crisp white accenting on the heel counter, midsole and mudguard. The sneaker is finished with subtle gold branding, displaying ‘Samoa’ in a debossed text above the Three-Stripes.

data.name: Disney x FortaRun CF Infant 'Mickey Mouse'
Superstars Foundation PS
data.story: The adidas Superstars Foundation PS is a version of the basketball-turned-streetwear classic, made for kids. Playing off the 1969 classic, this rendition arrives with a white leather upper, serrated Three-Stripes on the side and logo branding on the tongue and heel. The laces are elastic for easy on and off for little feet, while the Superstar's iconic rubber shell toe and traditional outsole round out the look.

data.name: FortaRun Infant 'Digi Camo'
data.story: Inspired by the brand's performance runners, the adidas FortaRun Infant 'Digi Camo' reworks the design with a military-style graphic. This kids' variant is presented in a mesh upper styled with an adjustable hook and loop strap with embedded Three-Stripes, synthetic toe skin and a heel tab. An EcoOrthoLite sockliner and a high-profile Cloudfoam midsole cushion the platform. A multidirectional tread pattern grips below.

data.name: RapidaZen I 'Pink'
data.story: Ideal for high-performance wear, the RapidaZen I 'Pink' sneaker blends adidas' innovative cushioning with kid-friendly design. The printed exterior is constructed of a stretch textile upper, reinforced with protective overlays. RapidaZen ditches the laces but adds a high tongue and elastic heel counter to provide growing feet simple, slip-on access. The shoe glides atop the Cloudfoam midsole and EVA outsole for cushioned steps.

data.story: The adidas Stan Smith Shoes update the classic comfort of the iconic design with kid-friendly adaptations. Constructed with a full grain leather upper, the shoe features a soft mesh and terry lining and three hook-and-loop straps at the midfoot in place of laces. The classic details of the original are maintained with a Stan Smith logo on the tongue, perforated Three-Stripes branding and a bright green leather heel tab, decorated with the brand’s Trefoil logo.

Blue and orange cover the upper, constructed of a stretch textile material. The laceless shoe features an elastic heel counter and high tongue to deliver uncomplicated, easy on-and-off style. Cloudfoam offers pillow-soft comfort, while the EVA outsole provides responsive impact protection.

The adidas AR 3.0 Infant is a kids'-sized version of the shoe, coming mainly in black with pink on the laces and midsole. The upper features durable overlays, dual stitching and a Velcro strapping system around the ankle and heel for a great fit.

The knit triangle pattern on the heel and large mid-foot strap adds depth and texture to the monochromatic red colorway. Subtle Three-Stripes branding is embossed into the suede-like upper. The high ankle provides support, and the combo of the large strap and lacing secure growing feet on the move.

At the toe, the durable shell-toe design reinforces support while metallic gold 'Superstar' lettering on the sidewall adds flair.
